README -- describes contents of GeosApm directory
11 Mar 2011
Bob Yantosca
geos-chem-support@as.harvard.edu


The following files are lightly touched by the APM microphysics code and
therefore can be kept in the GeosCore/ directory:

aerosol_mod.f
chemdr.f
cleanup.f
convection_mod.f
diag1.f
diag3.f
diag_mod.f
initialize.f
input_mod.f
isoropiaII_mod.f
ndxx_setup.f
rpmares_mod.f
tpcore_bc_mod.f
tracer_mod.f
tracerid_mod.f
transport_mod.f


However, these files contain major modifications for APM and are better
isolated in the GeosApm directory for the time being:

a3_read_mod.f
a6_read_mod.f
apm_coag_mod.f
apm_driv_mod.f
apm_grow_mod.f
apm_init_mod.f
apm_nucl_mod.f
apm_phys_mod.f
apm_wets_mod.f
carbon_mod.f
chemistry_mod.f
dao_mod.f
drydep_mod.f
dust_dead_mod.f
dust_mod.f
main.f
restart_mod.f
seasalt_mod.f
sulfate_mod.f
wetscav_mod.f


In the future, we will work towards achieving a more clean separation of 
APM code from GEOS-Chem code.  This will be a necessary step for creating
the 1-D column GEOS-Chem mode.